Text: How can you make your games more accessible for everyone, especially in #VR? In our Creator Spotlight series, the Owlchemy Labs team, behind the game Cosmonious High, gave us some accessible game design tips and insight:üé® For color blindness accessibility, they added different facets to some of the puzzles. In a mini-game where the player matches crystals of the same color, they also have a distinct pattern and shape so anyone can complete it.üí° ‚ÄúDesign for one, extend to many‚Äù. When you create something accessible for one person, it‚Äôll likely benefit more people than you had in mind. For example, empowering one-handed players by making the second controller optional, also meant anyone could play while holding a snack, a drink, or even if one of the controllers was out of battery!Find more insights in our new blog about accessibility in VR: https://on.unity.com/3HgetUT
